LoaderStreamChannel<OUT> - Interface in com.github.dm.jrt.android.v11.stream
Interface defining a stream output channel, that is, a channel concatenating map and reduce functions, employing Android loaders to run the backing routines.
In fact, each function in the channel is backed by a routine instance, that can have its own specific configuration and invocation mode.
In order to prevent undesired leaks, the class of the specified functions must have a static scope.

with(LoaderContext) - Method in interface com.github.dm.jrt.android.v11.stream.LoaderStreamChannel
Sets the stream loader context.
The context will be used by all the concatenated routines until changed.
If null it will cause the next routines to employ the configured runner instead of an Android loader.
